Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance, which protects the driver in the event of an accident, represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of driving license, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive the agreed insurance amount in a certain amount for taking care of the payment of damages in the event of an insured event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies concluded that married people have fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of rides and thus the likelihood of having an accident.
The increase in frequency of rides increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when determining the cost of insurance premiums.
Therefore, the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the kind of insurance that best corresponds to his profile of the insured.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to meeting the type of insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 face various disadvantages, such as having little driving experience and short driving licenses, when they want to arrange insurance premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most careful drivers can choose insurance against all risks with a premium discount to get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would involve the participation of the client in the payment of the insured event.
“The part of the payment of the insured event that the client will provide will be determined in advance when determining the premium price, which will be the higher the lower the participation,” explains Luis Noguera, Chief Executive Officer of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants in the operation so that the client insures against damage caused to other persons, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under 25 years old, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
Malus, on the other hand, is an increase in the basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profit.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus,” Noguera explains.
After crossing the twenty-five-year limit, it is easier for drivers to get insurance, as the risk index of the client decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks with a discount.
“Young people usually can’t take advantage of the lessons learned when an accident occurs, or even when driving,” assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of the procedure, when the “fear of the newcomer” has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies as the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which could amount to 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other participants in the operation, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
“Their driving is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount,” notes Luis Noguera.
Retirees are advised to have insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which is <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>150) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would be most suitable for us in view of our personal situation.
