Two months ago, when the prime minister avoided calling elections and insulted British intelligence by claiming that this decision was not influenced by polls, there was hope that he would secure a resilient and effective government.
Instead of being articulated by the increasingly amusing Liberal Democrat deputy chairman, the once feared Mr. Brown changed from Stalin to Mr. Bean.
